        "content": "<p>How can I set a auxiliary variable, to give a whole part names, in order to simplify the proof? Thanks!</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- just example to show motivation:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- let x' := x + 1</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- rw [‚Üê x'] -- it surely won't work</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"c1\">-- exact (rfl x')</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
